<head>COSMIC FORCE</head>
    <list type="translations">
        <item xml:lang="zh">陰陽氣</item>
    </list>
<div type="definition">
<p>FORCE, PRINCIPLE, OR ELEMENT which CONTROLS PERCEIVED PHENOMENA in the WORLD.</p>
    </div>
<div type="notes">
<div type="old-chinese-criteria">
<p>1. The most general term for physical principles operative in the dynamics of natural processes is qì 氣.</p>
<p>2. Yīn 陰 refers to the female, dark principle in Chinese naturalist and cosmological speculation.</p>
<p>3. Yáng 陽 refers to the male, bright principle in Chinese naturalist and cosmological speculation.</p>
<p>4. Dào 道 is sometimes used to refer to the quintessential material/energetic basis for cosmic development.</p>
<p>5. Lǐ 理 is sometimes used as a general concept referring to all manner of basic cosmic forces.</p>
        </div>
<div type="modern-chinese-criteria">
<p>陰陽</p>
<p>氣</p>
<p>rough draft to BEGIN TO identify synonym group members for analysis, based on CL etc. 18.11.2003. CH ／</p>
        </div>
